title: Milwaukee Cycling Center TT Series Presented by Team Velocause
Hollander/Benelux Sussex Criterium
registration:
Pre-register at www.usacycling.org or www.wicycling.org
Day of event, registration opens at 8:15am and closes 15 minutes prior to each event. Sorry no refunds.
notes:
Bike donation to Dream-Bikes gets free entry to 1 race!
Sussex Criterium is held under USAC event permit and USAC rules will apply. WCA scoring and rules apply.
Racers can choose to race additional races under USAC rules for an additional $10 per race, $5 for juniors.
All fees include USAC insurance and WCA surcharges. Riders without a USA Cycling racing license must purchase a “USAC One Day License” for $10. U23 points will be scored in the Women Open and Men P/1/2/3 races. Helmets are required at all times when riding your bike on the race site.
directions:
From the North - Exit Hwy 41/45 at Silver Spring Rd. and head west continue through Sussex to Hwy 164 and take a left on Hwy 164. Take a left onto Hwy K. Take the next left and enter the Sussex Corporate Center.

From the East or West - exit 194 at Hwy 164 and head north. Continue Northbound on Hwy 164 to Hwy K and take a right on Hwy K. Take the next left and enter the corporate center.

Midwest Cyclocross Regional Championship
description: USA Cycling Midwest Cyclocross Championships & Midwest Grand Prix. Saturday December 17th USA Cycling will crown the best in the Midwest.
course: L5 racing, will be brining back the historic Angell park speedway which has in the past hosted The US Gand Prix of Cyclocross
registration:
When: December 17 & 18th. On Dec. 17 USAC will award the best in each category of Cyclocross. 

December 18th Midwest Grand Prix will be a non-championship race, but will offer the same level of difficulty and fun.

Prizes: Saturday Medals to Top 3 in each Category. Sunday, Prizes and cash payout to select categories. 

VIP Parking: $2 

Team Space: $20 for the weekend. This is as many tents as you want on pit row, but only one vehicle and trailer will be allowed in this area. 

Where: Angel Park Speedway 315 Park St, Sun Prairie, WI 53590
